The paper deals with a computer vision problem of scene labeling and proposes a novel approach using deep residual networks and recurrent neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the training of the proposed model from scratch, which suggests the involvement of machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also involves the modeling of long-range contextual dependence, which can be related to the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as scene labeling, which can be related to the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
